  <h1>
    Project
  </h1>

  <p>
    From 2021 onwards our strategy towards Activation was to 
    <mark>connect the customer to the full value of Dropbox.</mark>
    My teams set out to create an activation experience that scaled for multiple
    products and increased offerings — this is how we did it.
  </p>

  <h2>
    Developing a strategy
  </h2>

  <p>
    Using an
    <%= link_to "inclusive development framework",
      "#inclusive-high-level-planning" %>,
    me and my EPD lead partners
    set out to develop the first pass of a high level strategy.
    <mark>We began by identifying the problems worth solving. </mark>
    We leveraged existing research and conducted
    new research, including some that I specifically requested.
    We analyzed data from past A/B tests; many
    of which were derived from strategies I wrote.
  </p>

  <p>
    We engaged our Customer Experience
    team, talked with customers, and monitored our forums.
    We discovered that 
    <mark> 
    customers were not finding value beyond the basic file, sync, and share
    functionalities. </mark>
    We also noticed that the user experience was negatively affected by frequent
    upsells, eroding the trust of our users. Furthermore, the complexity of our
    foundational features was driving customers away.
  </p>

