  <h1>
    Planning and process
  </h1>

  <p>
    I often leverage principles, values, and process to improve outcomes.
    For this project, I'll highlight a few process improvements I made.
  </p>

  <h2>
    Establishing Rituals
  </h2>
  <p>
    With a mild gap in soluiton quality, <mark>I kicked off several
    rituals to empower feedback, collaboration, innovation,
    alignment, and big picture thinking. </mark>
    This was an ongoing practice and wasn’t done once.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Bi-weekly Design critiques (for feedback and quality)
    </li>
    <li>
      Weekly Design studio time (for x-fn collaboration)
    </li>
    <li>
      Weekly Design calibration (for design quality calibration)
    </li>
    <li>
      Quarterly vision sprints (for x-fn future thinking)
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>
    Leveraging Data & Resesarch
  </h2>
  <p>
    Using data to inform design decisions wasn't a skillset many in the
    team possesed.
    I took 2 steps to address this.
    <mark>
    The first step was to
    help designers build a relationship with data.</mark>
    I did so by making a specific ask;
    pair with a Data Scientist between projects
    and work together to come up with a list of assumptions.
    <mark>The second step was to build more design rigor into
      our A/B testing processes.</mark>
    In critiques, and 1:1s, I would
    focus on the simple things like isolating design
    variables and designing with intent to learn.
  </p>
  <p>
  </p>

  <a name="inclusive-high-level-planning"></a>
  <h2>
    Inclusive High Level Planning
  </h2>
  <p>
    Including all voices creates connection to the product.
    <mark>To develop strategy I lobbied for, and employed, a
    combined tops down, bottoms up, approach</mark> that would 
    allow everyone to contribute.
  </p>
  <p>
    We landed on the “W” approach.
    Leads would establish a foundational direction from existing
    information, contributions and feedback came from squads, and back up and
    down until we had a high level plan for the year.
  </p>

  <h1>
    Design ❤️
  </h1>

