        and when, to use each component.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </div>

  <h1>
    Learnings
  </h1>

  <h2>
    Activation should be targeted when possible.
  </h2>

  <p>
    As the offerings of a product grows, so does the audience and their needs.
    <mark>As the audience becomes more complex the array
    of jobs-to-be-done expands and a one size fits all approach
    for activation loses it's effectiveness.</mark>
    A combination of general activation (what you do with less knowledge of the
    customer) and targeted activation (knowledge based) is
    an effective way to scale an activation experience as a product grows.
  </p>

  <h2>
    Bad incentives make bad products.
  </h2>

  <p>
    <mark>Goals drive outcomes more than principles.</mark>
    And misaligned goals can drive bad outcomes regardlress of intention.
    If goals are
    misaligned there is a high risk that one team’s work can negatively impact
    that of another’s.
    Make sure that goals across your group or company are aligned!
  </p>

  <h2>
    Speed can be a valuable constraint.
  </h2>

  <p>
    When we forced time constraints, our rigor went up, our scope down.
    <mark>Speed
    became a valuable constraint to keep us from over investing in ideas that
    weren’t validated.</mark> This learning inspired 
    <%= link_to raw("a value of mine &mdash; Encourage Deadlines."), 
      values_path(anchor: 'encourage-deadlines') %>
  </p>

